race.comment: Decimated by scratchings with half the field missing. I'MATEEZ (3) is one of the more experienced in the field and looks overdue for a win. Fresh-up raced on speed and boxed on well to place. Fitter and drawn ideally. Will give a sight again.  EYES OF BLUE (17) was in the market on debut over 1000m at Ballarat and eventually found the lead, turned there, and boxed on fairly to finish a three length fifth. Better for the run and the smaller field suits now. Expected to take running down again. MAJESTIC CHOICE (11) is a well bred filly by leading sire Extreme Choice making debut. Presents fitter for two jump-outs and off the low draw is worth respecting any market moves. PUNIC WAR (5) finished in the placings before a break and resumes off a jump-out win. Should run well fresh.
race.rail_position: +4m from the 400m to the winning post, True Remainder. (Pent: 5.60)
